On the economic front, workable economic recovery strategies are required to reboot the economy, including deliberate efforts in developing household savings and financial literacy.
 Economic recovery funds, incentives and innovativeness of the private sector should be used to structure win-win public private partnerships (PPPs). PPPs are low-hanging fruits in leveraging money quickly into direct employment creation that is highly needed at this stage in our lives.





This should begin by financing already vetted and approved projects, which are easily activatable and can circumvent typical delays.
Such projects can enhance connectivity to already developed infrastructure, including accelerating development of rural access roads to boost agriculture. This will make voters more enlightened.
